<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Larry Fink letter</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266632/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxhY2tyb2NrLmNvbS9=
1cy9pbmRpdmlkdWFsLzIwMjItbGFycnktZmluay1jZW8tbGV0dGVy/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB06be2f3b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">this</a>=C2=A0isn=E2=80=99t very helpful:</p><blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Delivering on the competing interests of a=
 company=E2=80=99s many divergent stakeholders is not easy. As a CEO, I kno=
w this firsthand. In this polarized world, CEOs will invariably have one se=
t of stakeholders demanding that we do one thing, while another set of stak=
eholders demand that we do just the opposite.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">That is why it is more important than ever that your company and its man=
agement be guided by its purpose. If you stay true to your company=E2=80=99=
s purpose and focus on the long term, while adapting to this new world arou=
nd us, you will deliver durable returns for shareholders and help realize t=
he power of capitalism for all.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">I suppose if you are the chief executive officer of a public company you =
will sometimes find yourself in a situation where some of your stakeholders=
 demand that you do one thing while another set of stakeholders demand that=
 you do just the opposite. And you might say, well, one of our important st=
akeholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0not the=C2=A0<em>most=C2=A0</em>important probabl=
y, not up there with customers or employees, but certainly important =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0is Larry Fink, who runs BlackRock Inc., which is among our biggest=
 shareholders, as it is for almost every public company. And so you might c=
all Larry Fink up and say =E2=80=9Chey Larry I got some people who want me =
to double down on producing thermal coal and I got some other people who wa=
nt me to get out of the thermal coal business, what do=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</=
em>think I should do?=E2=80=9D And Fink will be like =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Cstay true to your company=E2=80=99s purpose and focus on the long term=
=E2=80=9D? Okay? =E2=80=9CLarry, I gotta be honest with you, my company=E2=
=80=99s purpose is mining thermal coal, that=E2=80=99s just what we do, but=
 the long-term prospects for thermal coal are not so hot; should I stick to=
 our purpose, fulfill it, pay out some dividends and disappear, or should I=
 try to pivot into wind farms?=E2=80=9D I feel like Larry Fink <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266632/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDEtMTQvYmxhY2tyb2NrLWhhc=
y1ncmVlbi1wbGFucz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTE4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWls=
JnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjAxMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV=
5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB875f4b80" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> has a preference</a> h=
ere! But he is just one stakeholder among many.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s Fink=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266632/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxhY2tyb2NrLmNvbS9=
1cy9pbmRpdmlkdWFsLzIwMjItbGFycnktZmluay1jZW8tbGV0dGVy/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cC06be2f3b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">annual letter to CEOs</a>, which I quoted above. =E2=
=80=9CThe Power of Capitalism=E2=80=9D is the title?=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t r=
eally know who the audience is here? CEOs? I am not sure how actionable it =
is, for a CEO. The famous problem of stakeholder capitalism, as Fink says,=
=C2=A0is that while it is=C2=A0<em>relatively=C2=A0</em>easy to figure out =
what shareholders are supposed to want =E2=80=94=C2=A0stocks that go up =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0it is much harder to figure out what all your stakeholders want=
=C2=A0and how to prioritize them. If as a CEO you say =E2=80=9CI work for t=
he shareholders and I do what I can to make the stock go up,=E2=80=9D then =
you pretty much know what you have to do. Memes, is the answer, it turns ou=
t: <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266632=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMDQvbW=
FjeS1zLXRhcmdldGVkLWJ5LW1lbWUtYWN0aXZpc3RzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTgyMl9NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDEx=
OCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe83ef2d8" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> What you have to do is meme stuff</a>. Crypto, electric vehicles, non-f=
ungible tokens, that sort of thing.=C2=A0I=E2=80=99m sorry! I don=E2=80=99t=
 like it either. But this is a question that is subject to empirical analys=
is. Whereas if you work for the stakeholders then, you know, which stakehol=
ders and=C2=A0when? Your only guidepost is to =E2=80=9Cstay true to your co=
mpany=E2=80=99s focus,=E2=80=9D which does not necessarily answer all of yo=
ur practical questions, though it probably=C2=A0<em>will=C2=A0</em>stop you=
 from messing around with NFTs.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably =
the audience is really BlackRock=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>clients</em>, the peopl=
e and institutions whose trillions of dollars of retirement savings are man=
aged by BlackRock. One model for Fink=E2=80=99s annual letter is that he ha=
s cranked up the environmental, social and governance stuff, in the letters=
 and elsewhere, for the past few years, because ESG is hot in the investmen=
t-management industry and talking about it attracts clients. But there are =
vague <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266=
632/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wMS8xOC9idXNpbmVzcy9kZWFsYm9vay9=
maW5rLWJsYWNrcm9jay13b2tlLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd2304e67" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>rumblings of a backlash</a>, of clients=C2=A0and politicians worrying that=
 BlackRock is =E2=80=9Ctoo =E2=80=98woke,=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D so he=E2=80=99s=
 dialing it back like 10% in this letter:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Stakeholder capitalism is not about politics. It is not a social=
 or ideological agenda. It is not =E2=80=9Cwoke.=E2=80=9D <em>It is capital=
ism</em>, driven by mutually beneficial relationships between you and the e=
mployees, customers, suppliers, and communities your company relies on to p=
rosper. This is the power of capitalism.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;"><strong>In today=E2=80=99s globally interconnected world, a company mus=
t create value for and be valued by its full range of stakeholders in order=
 to deliver long-term value for its shareholders.</strong> It is through ef=
fective stakeholder capitalism that capital is efficiently allocated, compa=
nies achieve durable profitability, and value is created and sustained over=
 the long-term. Make no mistake, the fair pursuit of profit is still what a=
nimates markets; and long-term profitability is the measure by which market=
s will ultimately determine your company=E2=80=99s success.</p></blockquote=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to read that passage is =E2=80=9Cwe w=
ould still like to manage money for Republicans too.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is kind of a boring letter? There is something od=
d about the world=E2=80=99s largest=C2=A0<em>shareholder=C2=A0</em>advocati=
ng for stakeholder capitalism, saying to corporate CEOs =E2=80=9Cno, <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26404004.266632/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMDQvZmFjZWJvb2s=
td2hpc3RsZWJsb3dlci1zaG93cy1hLXNoaWZ0LWluLXNoYXJlaG9sZGVyLXZhbHVlcy1hd2F5LW=
Zyb20tcHJvZml0cz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTE4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJ=
nV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjAxMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5=
c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb90d7b37" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> don=E2=80=99t put share=
holders first</a>, prioritize your workers and customers and communities ab=
ove shareholder profits.=E2=80=9D But of course he=E2=80=99s not saying tha=
t. The point of this year=E2=80=99s letter is to dispel the idea that he mi=
ght be saying that. He=E2=80=99s saying that sometimes having good customer=
 service, paying employees enough to motivate them, and not breaking the la=
w can help maximize the long-term value of a company=E2=80=99s cash flows=
=C2=A0<em>to shareholders</em>, and so companies should do those things. Th=
eir executives should run the company, you know, <em>well</em>, like a busi=
ness. They should make good choices and not bad ones, so that the business =
is valuable, for its shareholders, who are Fink=E2=80=99s clients. There is=
 nothing here that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/26404004.266632/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMTgtMDktMjcvc2hhcmVob2xkZXItdmFsdWUtY291bGQtYmUtd29yc2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDExO=
DIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRt=
X3Rlcm09MjIwMTE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd=
fcde0f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> Milton Friedman</a> could possibly object to.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are, in the world, investors who specialize in f=
inding companies that make money but spend it wastefully on businesses with=
 poor long-term prospects, buy up shares in those companies and push them t=
o cut that spending and return cash to shareholders who can put it to bette=
r uses. There are, in the world, investors who specialize in finding compan=
ies that don=E2=80=99t make any money but that have bold and achievable lon=
g-term dreams, buy up shares in those companies and give them funding to tu=
rn those dreams into reality. There are investors who specialize in some in=
dustry and try to pick which firms in that industry will thrive in the long=
 run and which will fail. BlackRock is not one of those investors =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0or, rather, it does a bit of all of those things, but <em>as a whole =
</em>it specializes in (1) finding all of the companies, (2) buying like 7%=
 of their stock and (3) holding it forever.[1]=C2=A0=C2=A0And then Fink=C2=
=A0writes an annual letter to=C2=A0<em>all of them at once</em>. How nuance=
d can that one letter be? =E2=80=9CTry to do a good job=E2=80=9D is pretty =
broadly applicable advice, but beyond that situations will differ. Even =E2=
=80=9Ctry to manage your company for the long term=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cst=
ay true to your company=E2=80=99s purpose,=E2=80=9D generic as they sound, =
can conflict with each other.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also here=E2=
=80=99s this:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We see a growing =
interest among shareholders =E2=80=93 including among our own clients =E2=
=80=93 in the corporate governance of public companies.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">That is why we are pursuing an initiative to use technology to=
 give more of our clients the option to have a say in how proxy votes are c=
ast at companies their money is invested in. We now offer this option to ce=
rtain institutional clients, including pension funds that support 60 millio=
n people. We are working to expand that universe.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">We are committed to a future where every investor =E2=80=93 even ind=
ividual investors =E2=80=93 can have the option to participate in the proxy=
 voting process if they choose.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We know the=
re are significant regulatory and logistical hurdles to achieving this toda=
y, but we believe this could bring more democracy and more voices to capita=
lism. Every investor deserves the right to be heard. We will continue to pu=
rsue innovation and work with other market participants and regulators to h=
elp advance this vision toward reality.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">One way to put it is that right now Larry Fink gets to decide how=
 trillions of dollars=E2=80=99 worth of shares are voted at corporate meeti=
ngs, and he is volunteering to give up that power and hand it back to his c=
lients (eventually). Do you think a fully distributed BlackRock, one where =
each client votes its own shares rather than delegating that power to Larry=
 Fink, would be as influential as the current actual BlackRock? Would its l=
etters get as much attention?</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-conte=
