people those nine-figure payouts.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
You take a chunk for yourself.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This i=
s a good trade =E2=80=94=C2=A0build a spigot of government money and plant =
yourself in front of it =E2=80=94=C2=A0but still you could improve it. As I=
 said above, it is good for a regulator to develop a reputation for toughne=
ss, in part because that will get you continuing respect from the people st=
ill in government administering the spigot. And of course spigots of govern=
ment money are controversial and could be shut off at any time=C2=A0due to =
budget problems etc. So what you want to do is replace Step 1 above with:</=
p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0=
;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You work in government and design a=
 program that very toughly takes nine-figure sums from bad private-sector a=
ctors and then gives a share of them to good private-sector actors, but onl=
